articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Parnas, 'on the hook criminally,' makes surprising choice to give TV interview: MSNBC legal analyst
articles.description: Berit Berger and Maya Wiley, both formerly of the Southern District of New York, react to the news that Giuliani associate Lev Parnas is being interviewed by Rachel Maddow.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: House votes to send articles of impeachment to the Senate
articles.description: The House of Representatives has voted to send articles of impeachment against President Trump to the Senate. NBC News' Garrett Haake reports on what happens next from Capitol Hill.

articles.author: Steve Benen
articles.title: On impeachment, head-in-the-sand stance now even harder to defend
articles.description: The latest evidence in Trump's Ukraine scandal just made it tougher for Mitch McConnell to stick to his head-in-the-sand posture.
